abstract: The new Conservative government plans to pass a law restricting local authorities from participating in the Boycott, Divestment and Sanctions movement.
snippet: The new Conservative government plans to pass a law restricting local authorities from participating in the Boycott, Divestment and Sanctions movement.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — Britain’s newly elected Conservative government plans to ban local authorities from taking part in the boycott-Israel movement, a British official said, following the lead of American officials who have also sought to clamp down on the campaign to pressure Israel to change its policies toward the Palestinians.

abstract: Cuba's Communist government is prepared if the administration of U.S. President Donald Trump decides to sever diplomatic relations although it hopes that does not come to pass, a top Cuban diplomat said on Monday.
snippet: Cuba's Communist government is prepared if the administration of U.S. President Donald Trump decides to sever diplomatic relations although it hopes that does not come to pass, a top Cuban diplomat said on Monday.
lead_paragraph: HAVANA — Cuba's Communist government is prepared if the administration of U.S. President Donald Trump decides to sever diplomatic relations although it hopes that does not come to pass, a top Cuban diplomat said on Monday.
headline_main: Cuba Says It Is Prepared if U.S. Chooses to Sever Diplomatic Ties
headline_print_headline: Cuba Says It Is Prepared if U.S. Chooses to Sever Diplomatic Ties

abstract: A U.S. judge on Monday flatly rejected a last-ditch bid by President Donald Trump's former national security adviser Michael Flynn to get the criminal charge to which he already pleaded guilty dropped, brushing aside his claims of misconduct by prosecutors and the FBI.
snippet: A U.S. judge on Monday flatly rejected a last-ditch bid by President Donald Trump's former national security adviser Michael Flynn to get the criminal charge to which he already pleaded guilty dropped, brushing aside his claims of misconduct by pr...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A U.S. judge on Monday flatly rejected a last-ditch bid by President Donald Trump's former national security adviser Michael Flynn to get the criminal charge to which he already pleaded guilty dropped, brushing aside his claims of misconduct by prosecutors and the FBI.
headline_main: Judge Rejects Claims by Trump Ex-Adviser Flynn of FBI Misconduct
headline_print_headline: Judge Rejects Claims by Trump Ex-Adviser Flynn of FBI Misconduct

abstract: The prime minister and his party question the broadcaster’s reliance on fees paid by viewers. They are increasingly at odds with its journalism, too.
snippet: The prime minister and his party question the broadcaster’s reliance on fees paid by viewers. They are increasingly at odds with its journalism, too.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — The British Broadcasting Corporation has long been one of Britain’s most revered institutions. But after an election campaign in which it faced charges of bias, the media organization finds its future in the hands of some of its biggest critics.

abstract: Congress would raise the U.S. tobacco purchasing age to 21 and permanently repeal several of the Affordable Care Act's (ACA) taxes under a massive government spending bill unveiled on Monday.
snippet: Congress would raise the U.S. tobacco purchasing age to 21 and permanently repeal several of the Affordable Care Act's (ACA) taxes under a massive government spending bill unveiled on Monday.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Congress would raise the U.S. tobacco purchasing age to 21 and permanently repeal several of the Affordable Care Act's (ACA) taxes under a massive government spending bill unveiled on Monday.
headline_main: U.S. Spending Deal Would Raise Tobacco Age, Deny Some Trump Border Wall Money
headline_print_headline: U.S. Spending Deal Would Raise Tobacco Age, Deny Some Trump Border Wall Money

abstract: New York’s law allowing undocumented immigrants to obtain licenses went into effect on Monday. The same day, New Jersey passed a similar bill.
snippet: New York’s law allowing undocumented immigrants to obtain licenses went into effect on Monday. The same day, New Jersey passed a similar bill.
lead_paragraph: On the New York side of the Hudson River, lines outside some Department of Motor Vehicles offices stretched for blocks on Monday, as people sought to take advantage of a new state law allowing undocumented immigrants to obtain driver’s licenses.

abstract: Democrats in the key swing state of Wisconsin vowed Monday to redouble efforts to ensure that any voters whose registrations have been nullified by a judge's recent ruling will be able to register again before the 2020 presidential election.
snippet: Democrats in the key swing state of Wisconsin vowed Monday to redouble efforts to ensure that any voters whose registrations have been nullified by a judge's recent ruling will be able to register again before the 2020 presidential election.
lead_paragraph: MADISON, Wis. — Democrats in the key swing state of Wisconsin vowed Monday to redouble efforts to ensure that any voters whose registrations have been nullified by a judge's recent ruling will be able to register again before the 2020 presidential election.
headline_main: Wisconsin Democrats Vow to Register Voters Who May Be Purged
headline_print_headline: Wisconsin Democrats Vow to Register Voters Who May Be Purged

abstract: White House economic adviser Larry Kudlow said on Monday he would visit Britain in early January for economic and trade talks following the victory of British Prime Minister Boris Johnson's Conservative Party in last Thursday's election.
snippet: White House economic adviser Larry Kudlow said on Monday he would visit Britain in early January for economic and trade talks following the victory of British Prime Minister Boris Johnson's Conservative Party in last Thursday's election.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — White House economic adviser Larry Kudlow said on Monday he would visit Britain in early January for economic and trade talks following the victory of British Prime Minister Boris Johnson's Conservative Party in last Thursday's election.
headline_main: White House Adviser to Visit Britain Next Month for Trade Talks
headline_print_headline: White House Adviser to Visit Britain Next Month for Trade Talks
